<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1439,645,1135]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">
All members of 
<emphasis box="[342,367,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[435,546,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Stipitatae</emphasis>
were previously classified under 
<emphasis box="[940,966,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1033,1328,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[1033,1275,645,670]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sensu">
Platyspermum 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1210,1275,645,670]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" sensu="lato">sensu</taxonomicNameLabel>
</taxonomicName>
lato
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pascher, A." pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="109 - 131" refId="ref10037" refString="Pascher, A. (1904) Ubersicht uber die Arten der Gattung Gagea. Sitzungberichte des Deutschen naturwissenschaflichmedicischen Vereins fur Bohmen ' Lotos' 24: 109 - 131." type="journal article" year="1904">Pascher 1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pascher, A." box="[225,286,684,710]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="353 - 375" refId="ref10067" refString="Pascher, A. (1907) Conspectus Gagearum Asiae. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 19: 353 - 375." type="journal article" year="1907">1907</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stroh, G." box="[299,432,684,710]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="485 - 520" refId="ref10868" refString="Stroh, G. (1937) Die Gattung Gagea Salisb. Beihefte zum Botanischen Centralblatt 57: 485 - 520." type="journal article" year="1937">Stroh 1937</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Uphof, J. C." box="[445,588,684,710]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="163 - 176" refId="ref10976" refString="Uphof, J. C. (1958 - 1960) A review of the genus Gagea Salisb. I-III. Plantlife 14: 124 - 132, 151 - 161; 15: 163 - 176." type="journal article" year="1958">Uphof 1958</bibRefCitation>
â€“1960). 
<taxonomicName box="[685,947,684,710]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Stipitatae">
<emphasis box="[685,763,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Gagea</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[833,947,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Stipitatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[947,952,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">,</emphasis>
which comprises c. 60 species, is one of the largest sections in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wolfe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[409,487,722,747]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[409,487,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Gagea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(along with 
<emphasis box="[636,661,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wolfe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[727,805,722,747]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[727,805,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Gagea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[820,1057,722,748]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[928,987,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[1077,1328,722,748]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[1184,1243,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
included eight species from this section in their analyses. Since members of 
<emphasis box="[976,1005,761,786]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1074,1189,761,786]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Stipitatae</emphasis>
were placed in four subclades in a clade that corresponds to clade D in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[762,993,800,826]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[843,902,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
, this section must be merged with all other members of the clade D 
<taxonomicName authority="Zarrei et al. (2009)" authorityName="Zarrei" authorityYear="2009" box="[540,868,838,864]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sensu">
<emphasis box="[540,609,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[619,868,838,864]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[706,770,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Pascher (1907: 372)" authorityName="Pascher" authorityPageNumber="372" authorityYear="1907" box="[882,1395,838,864]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chomutovae">
<emphasis box="[882,1126,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Gagea chomutovae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pascher, A." box="[1136,1395,838,864]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="353 - 375" refId="ref10067" refString="Pascher, A. (1907) Conspectus Gagearum Asiae. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 19: 353 - 375." type="journal article" year="1907">Pascher (1907: 372)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityYear="1932" baseAuthorityName="Zucc." class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gageoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. gageoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greuter" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Royle" box="[333,531,877,902]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kunawurensis">
<emphasis box="[333,531,877,902]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. kunawurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were included in the anatomical studies as members of 
<emphasis box="[1216,1241,877,902]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1313,1428,877,902]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Stipitatae</emphasis>
. These species exhibited 
<typeStatus box="[460,513,916,942]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
II and III pedicels and 
<typeStatus box="[813,866,916,942]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
IV basal leaves (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Ingrouille, M. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1087,1332,916,942]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="155 - 177" refId="ref11602" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Ingrouille, M. J, Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2010 d) The systematic importance of anatomical data in Gagea (Liliaceae) from Flora Iranica area. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 164: 155 - 177." type="journal article" year="2010">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1175,1239,916,941]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
2010d
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascher" authorityYear="1907" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chomutovae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Gagea chomutovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityYear="1932" baseAuthorityName="Zucc." box="[324,492,954,979]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gageoides">
<emphasis box="[324,492,954,979]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. gageoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greuter" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Royle" box="[511,723,954,979]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kunawurensis">
<emphasis box="[511,723,954,979]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. kunawurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityYear="1946" box="[790,896,954,979]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exilis">
<emphasis box="[790,896,954,979]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. exilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of this section were included in a pollen morphological study by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S." box="[440,705,993,1019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="96 - 108" refId="ref11268" refString="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S. (2005) Pollen morphology of the genus Gagea (Liliaceae) in Iran. Flora 200: 96 - 108." type="journal article" year="2005">Zarrei &amp; Zarre (2005)</bibRefCitation>
; they exhibit 
<specimenCount box="[867,985,993,1019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" type="generic" typeStatus="types">four types</specimenCount>
of pollen that occur in other sections, so pollen characters do not support the monophyly of the section. Although there are several well-supported subclades composed of members of 
<emphasis box="[601,627,1071,1096]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[700,817,1071,1096]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Stipitatae</emphasis>
, this section on its own is polyphyletic. For more information, see 
<emphasis box="[348,374,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wolfe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[441,519,1109,1134]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[441,519,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Gagea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[576,594,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G</emphasis>
. sect. 
<emphasis box="[668,772,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Minimae</emphasis>
below.
</paragraph>
